789 West End Avenue at S.E. corner of 99th Street, a new apartment building replacing six old houses. The adjoining two small houses, together with the first of the houses which this replaces, are shown in a photograph of the middle of this block about 1912.
About 1915.
Irving Underhill, Photographer.
